we... we tend to believe the bodyguard.

29:21.468 --> 29:23.136
Include that in your conversation
with the D.A.

29:23.344 --> 29:25.889
But based on just the facts,
they’ll go after them for a plea deal,

29:26.139 --> 29:27.182
which might be a railroad.

29:28.600 --> 29:29.851
This way, Mr. Pregitzer.

29:31.436 --> 29:34.731
Give it to the D.A.’s office.
Let them decide what they want to do.

29:35.523 --> 29:38.359
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

29:42.530 --> 29:44.491
You’re covering for your son,
aren’t you, Mr. Pregitzer?

29:44.991 --> 29:47.869
Because when Dr. Miller called last night,
it wasn’t about some whore

29:47.952 --> 29:49.913
who got the wrong idea
because we looked into it,

29:49.996 --> 29:52.373
and there’s no indication
of any of that happening.

29:55.502 --> 29:56.961
Okay, then here’s what happens.

29:57.462 --> 30:00.256
This case goes to a grand jury.
This case goes public,

30:00.340 --> 30:02.383
and that... that secret

30:03.009 --> 30:05.386
that Eric has been working so hard
to keep a lid on,

30:05.678 --> 30:06.971
everybody’s gonna know.

30:07.931 --> 30:09.057
Do you want that for your son?

30:10.683 --> 30:12.435
Eric’s been through so much as it is...

30:13.394 --> 30:15.230
more than any person
should have to endure.

30:15.980 --> 30:17.524
Did Dr. Miller know about the sex change?

30:18.733 --> 30:21.653
-Did he perform it?
-He did the first one.

30:21.903 --> 30:23.988
-Which first one?
-When Eric was an infant.

30:24.405 --> 30:26.449
When he got circumcised,
there was an accident.

30:26.658 --> 30:31.079
-What kind of an accident, Mr. Pregitzer?
-The device that they used was electric.

30:31.663 --> 30:33.331
There was a malfunction,
and he was burned.

30:33.873 --> 30:38.211
The whole organ was... It was gone.

30:40.255 --> 30:43.758
And, uh, Dr. Miller?
He came into your life at that point?

30:44.092 --> 30:47.095
He heard about it somehow.
He approached me and my wife.

30:47.178 --> 30:49.639
He had this theory about
nature versus nurture,

30:49.722 --> 30:53.142
and, well, he assured us it would work.

30:53.560 --> 30:56.145
-So he performed the surgery on Eric?
-Yes.

30:57.397 --> 30:59.524
And... and it was part of
Dr. Miller’s theory

30:59.607 --> 31:02.360
that once we commitTed to it,
we could never tell Eric.

31:02.861 --> 31:06.823
Well, that didn’t work. In his heart,
Eric always knew that he was a boy.

31:06.948 --> 31:09.909
And... and so finally,
we told him when he was 18.

31:10.243 --> 31:12.996
Three years ago,
Eric tried to commit suicide.

31:13.204 --> 31:14.706
Dr. Miller wouldn’t leave him alone.

31:15.164 --> 31:18.334
And when Dr. Miller called him
and said he was coming over for a talk,

31:18.418 --> 31:21.296
that was too much for Eric to take
and that’s when I told him

31:21.754 --> 31:27.510
that if he ever tried
to contact Eric again, I’d kill him.

31:28.887 --> 31:30.597
Are you covering for your son,
Mr. Pregitzer?

31:31.097 --> 31:36.060
No. I went to Dr. Miller’s hotel
last night, I knocked on the door.

31:36.895 --> 31:39.105
He answered it, and I shot him.

31:41.274 --> 31:42.984
-All right...
-See, I’d forgiven Dr. Miller

31:43.067 --> 31:44.277
for what happened back then.

31:44.652 --> 31:46.905
We agreed to it.
it seemed like the only option.

31:48.615 --> 31:51.451
But when he kept popping up
into... into Eric’s life,

31:51.576 --> 31:54.829
well, I warned him. He wouldn’t listen.

31:55.038 --> 31:59.042
-Why wouldn’t he leave your son alone?
-I don’t know. I mean, he was obsessed.

31:59.667 --> 32:03.046
It was like... like
Eric was his Frankenstein or something.

32:04.005 --> 32:07.967
He kept wanting Eric to go public,
so he could go down in history,

32:08.051 --> 32:10.970
I... I guess. (SIGHS)

32:12.972 --> 32:14.057
I don’t know.

32:16.809 --> 32:17.977
All right, listen to me.

32:19.771 --> 32:22.273
We’re gonna go talk to Eric
to confirm this.

32:23.441 --> 32:26.110
Once we do, we’re gonna come back here
and help you with your statements.

32:26.319 --> 32:28.613
-You understand?
-Okay.

32:47.090 --> 32:48.424
-LAURA: What’s up, Ted?
-Hey.

32:48.716 --> 32:51.010
Remember, you asked me to keep an eye
on that King Tut character?

32:51.219 --> 32:52.220
Yeah. Anything?

32:52.345 --> 32:54.430
Did you give him any money
for cooperating?

32:54.555 --> 32:55.890
-Twenty bucks.
-Why?

32:56.140 --> 33:00.269
I just saw him walk into a hotel nearby
with all new gear and a hooker on his arm.

33:00.687 --> 33:03.064
-Which hotel?
-The Camden Arms over on second.

33:03.314 --> 33:04.440
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

33:04.774 --> 33:07.068
-You owe me a cold one for this.
-You got it.

33:11.239 --> 33:13.032
-JOHN: Is that what happened?
-Meaning what?

33:13.408 --> 33:15.368
You did this,
and your dad is covering for you.

33:15.660 --> 33:18.746
-No.
-You were home last night.

33:20.456 --> 33:23.626
Dr. Miller, he called me and said
he was planning on writing a book

33:23.710 --> 33:26.921
on the surgery, on my life,
how he saved me.

33:27.338 --> 33:32.885
He never got it. He’d just never admit it.
I always felt I was a boy.

33:33.011 --> 33:37.974
Here I was
wearing a dress, getting teased,

33:38.182 --> 33:41.728
just wishing, I was dead.

33:42.353 --> 33:44.856
Every year I’d go, and I’d have these
therapy sessions with him,

33:44.981 --> 33:46.816
and I’d tell him these things,
and he wouldn’t listen,

33:47.692 --> 33:49.193
even after my parents told me,

33:50.278 --> 33:55.658
and even after I had my sex changed back,
he’d never admit that he was wrong.

33:56.284 --> 33:58.995
He... he never apologized.

33:59.328 --> 34:01.330
Did you know your dad
was gonna go over there last night?

34:02.665 --> 34:07.795
No. All I did was tell him
that Dr. Miller had found me again,

34:07.920 --> 34:10.048
and he wanTed to write the book.

34:10.590 --> 34:14.635
My dad said he’d take care of it.
What’s gonna happen to my dad now?

34:16.012 --> 34:19.265
We’re gonna do everything we can to see
if this can go down as manslaughter.

34:19.640 --> 34:21.976
I don’t blame my dad
for what happened to me as a kid.

34:22.060 --> 34:23.936
I mean, they didn’t know what else to do.

34:24.312 --> 34:28.608
A... all I’m saying is, he’s not a killer.
He’s not a bad guy.

34:29.067 --> 34:32.070
But Dr. Miller wouldn’t leave me alone.

34:32.695 --> 34:34.822
All right. Wait here, okay?

34:39.118 --> 34:40.369
(DOOR OPENS)

34:41.621 --> 34:42.705
(SIGHS)

34:43.623 --> 34:46.084
I got an idea how to work this,
so just follow my lead.

34:46.209 --> 34:47.210
Fine.

34:47.877 --> 34:49.754
-(DOOR OPENS)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

34:50.004 --> 34:51.130
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

34:51.297 --> 34:52.715
JOHN: What the hell is going on here?

34:52.799 --> 34:54.842
Wait outside.
I’ll be with you in a minute.

34:54.967 --> 34:57.178
We’d like to have a
quick word with you, Lieutenant.

34:57.595 --> 35:02.558
-In a minute. Now, wait outside.
-No. we really need to talk, now.

35:02.725 --> 35:06.813
I’m not gonna say it again, Detective.
Now, get out of here.

35:16.322 --> 35:17.573
(SIGHS)

35:18.157 --> 35:20.034
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

35:21.953 --> 35:23.579
LAURA: Where’d you get the money
for all this?

35:24.122 --> 35:27.083
I told you.
I had a scratcher that played off big.

35:27.834 --> 35:31.212
-Where’d you buy it?
-At a bodega.

35:31.379 --> 35:33.422
-Where?
-Albuquerque.

35:33.881 --> 35:35.466
Where in the hell
do you think I bought it?

35:35.591 --> 35:38.219
-Here in the city.
-Let me ask you something, King.

35:38.553 --> 35:40.680
Where would you like to be headed to
in the next five minutes,

35:40.805 --> 35:44.642
back outdoors or down to
an eight by ten cell? And I’m not joking.

35:44.851 --> 35:48.855
I ain’t got no money. It’s all gone.
And you ain’t getting that back.

35:49.021 --> 35:51.899
-Where did you get it?
-From this white chick named Zoe,

35:52.024 --> 35:54.235
that was hanging out
with The Illness last night.

35:54.610 --> 35:55.736
Why’d she give it to you?

35:58.573 --> 36:01.534
Okay, now if the situation
had been just reversed,

36:01.701 --> 36:03.786
and that had been me laying
down there shot,

36:04.620 --> 36:07.498
and The Illness had been offered cash,
he would have done the same damn thing.

36:07.623 --> 36:09.542
So I ain’t got no guilt
on my consciousness.

36:09.709 --> 36:11.002
Why did Zoe give you money?

36:13.629 --> 36:15.882
I was headed back up
to the squat last night,

36:16.007 --> 36:19.886
and I see this crazy bitch
pointing a gun at The Illness

36:19.969 --> 36:22.263
and yelling,
"Say it again. say it again."

36:22.680 --> 36:24.724
Well, he must’ve said
what he wasn’t supposed to say

36:25.516 --> 36:28.644
’cause she went pow, pow, pow,
and The Illness was down.

36:30.313 --> 36:34.025
And I jumped back in the shadows.
And the dude that was with her,

36:34.275 --> 36:37.945
he came up and said something to her
and took the gun and boogied.

36:38.946 --> 36:41.199
And she just stood there.

36:42.408 --> 36:46.996
And I walked up to her, and I said,
"Girl, do you know what the hell

36:47.079 --> 36:48.581
"you just done?"

36:48.706 --> 36:49.874
And what’d she say?

36:49.957 --> 36:54.170
She’s yipping and yelling about
who knows what. Girl was high, y’all.

36:55.129 --> 36:57.381
She promised me money
if I kept her secret.

36:57.632 --> 36:59.508
And I said I had to think about it.

36:59.926 --> 37:04.430
She said, "5,000 dollars cash,"
and I said I was done thinking about it.

37:05.431 --> 37:10.186
And I met her in front of the liquor store
on Bleecker Street, 10:30 a.m.

37:10.561 --> 37:12.480
’Cause she said she had to wait
till her bank open.

37:16.442 --> 37:17.485
Wait here.

37:18.152 --> 37:19.237
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

37:20.404 --> 37:22.573
Before you say anything,
the timing of that sucked,

37:22.823 --> 37:23.866
and I’m sorry for that.

37:24.200 --> 37:26.702
Obviously, I would have preferred
that we’d had a chance to talk

37:26.786 --> 37:29.038
about a scenario like that
before it actually happened.

37:29.121 --> 37:30.623
What was your problem with what happened?

37:30.790 --> 37:32.833
How exactly were you gonna
help him with his statement?

37:33.376 --> 37:35.628
Were you gonna suggest that the D.O.A.
was threatening to kill him

37:36.170 --> 37:37.296
when he didn’t?

37:37.588 --> 37:39.840
Were you gonna tell him to say
that the D.O.A. came at him

37:39.966 --> 37:41.550
in a threatening manner,
when he hadn’t?

37:41.676 --> 37:43.844
Did you not hear
what the son went through?

37:43.928 --> 37:45.846
I did, and it’s messed up.

37:46.180 --> 37:48.516
And if this goes to trial,
the jury will hear it, too,

37:48.808 --> 37:50.268
and they’ll do their jobs.

37:50.434 --> 37:53.896
Are you gonna take statements for us now?
Hmm? Type the fives, testify in court?

37:54.272 --> 37:56.941
No. Because now we’re clear,
and something like that

37:57.024 --> 37:58.192
-won’t happen again.
-ANDY: Look.

37:58.442 --> 38:01.237
I don’t know how much contact you’ve had
with the real world

38:01.320 --> 38:02.947
while you were out there
locking up cops.

38:03.030 --> 38:06.701
-I had plenty of contact.
-Okay. having done this for a while...

38:06.784 --> 38:08.786
Make another comment
like that again, and you know?

38:09.245 --> 38:11.122
-We’re gonna have a real problem.
-ANDY: I’m sorry

38:11.289 --> 38:14.625
that came across wrong, Lieutenant.
It’s just that when you deal

38:14.709 --> 38:18.379
with a wide spectrum of people,
you sometimes come across a good person

38:18.462 --> 38:21.716
who did a bad thing.
Those people deserve consideration.

38:21.882 --> 38:24.427
And being able
to provide that consideration

38:24.552 --> 38:27.722
has been a long-standing tradition
in the New York City Police Department.

38:27.888 --> 38:29.932
Yeah, not to mention that in this,
station house is most times

38:30.057 --> 38:32.977
the only place in the whole system
where justice is really done.

38:33.519 --> 38:37.440
In a fender bender, maybe.
But not when it involves murder.

38:37.940 --> 38:40.651
In that circumstance,
your job as a detective

38:40.818 --> 38:43.904
is to ascertain what happened
and then document what happened.

38:44.613 --> 38:50.077
Your job's not to reinterpret or re-create
the facts of a homicide as you see fit.

38:51.871 --> 38:55.374
I’m sorry, but this conversation is over.
Kick the son, process the dad.

38:55.750 --> 38:58.294
(PHONE DIALING)

38:58.878 --> 39:00.004
We’re done, guys.

39:06.344 --> 39:09.430
(CLEARS THROAT)
I got 32 years on this job.

39:09.972 --> 39:14.602
I always planned on leaving on my terms,
and that day’s not too far away.

39:14.894 --> 39:18.689
But if I can’t do my job,
one that I can live with morally,

39:19.565 --> 39:20.900
then I’m out the door.

39:21.233 --> 39:23.569
Oh, eventually that’s a decision
that every cop has to make.

39:24.820 --> 39:25.905
It’s never an easy one.

39:29.033 --> 39:31.327
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

39:36.499 --> 39:39.293
-Andy, you drive your car today?
-Yeah.

39:39.418 --> 39:40.753
You’re not gonna like this.

39:42.046 --> 39:43.214
(SIGHS)

39:48.928 --> 39:52.139
-(CAR HONKING)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

39:57.770 --> 39:58.979
You got to be kidding me.

40:01.190 --> 40:02.775
(SIGHS)

40:05.736 --> 40:07.571
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

40:07.696 --> 40:08.823
P.A.B.

40:10.324 --> 40:13.285
What’s it say? Andy?

40:14.620 --> 40:16.122
"Payback’s a bitch."

40:16.539 --> 40:18.999
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(CAR HONKING)

40:22.253 --> 40:25.506
This isn’t a joke. (BREATHES HEAVILY)

40:38.018 --> 40:39.645
-Where’s Zoe?
-With her attorney.

40:39.812 --> 40:41.522
We’ll get her
to central booking afterwards.

40:41.605 --> 40:44.567
Desk sergeant told me
you had a cop keeping an eye on a witness.

40:44.859 --> 40:47.361
-Yeah. Cop’s name was Ted Kio.
-That’s really heads-up.

40:47.486 --> 40:49.238
I’ll put a good word in for you
with the chief.

40:49.447 --> 40:52.074
Or you could just put a good word
in for Ted. He did all the legwork.

40:54.285 --> 40:56.704
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

40:59.373 --> 41:01.000
Well, it was a little rocky today,

41:01.667 --> 41:03.377
but it’s important
that you all know something.

41:03.544 --> 41:05.838
No disrespect to former bosses,

41:06.172 --> 41:08.549
but I was sent here
to replace Sergeant Gibson

41:08.674 --> 41:12.052
because it’s the department’s perception
that this is a rogue outfit.

41:12.678 --> 41:16.098
So, I come with a specific mandate
from my bosses

41:16.515 --> 41:21.187
to make this squad reflect today’s job,
today’s policing.

41:21.604 --> 41:22.730
And it’s gonna happen.

41:23.856 --> 41:27.109
So I ask that you join me in accomplishing
what I’ve been instructed to do.

41:27.568 --> 41:30.446
In return, you’ll have
my complete allegiance and support.

41:30.571 --> 41:34.408
If you elect not to,
you won’t be working here anymore.

41:34.617 --> 41:38.329
I’m afraid it’s that simple and I hope
that doesn’t happen for anyone here.

41:39.538 --> 41:41.499
Have a good night. I’ll see you tomorrow.

41:42.958 --> 41:44.793
(FOOTSETEPS FADING)

41:45.044 --> 41:48.088
-(JOHN LAUGHS)
-All right. Can it, John.

41:48.255 --> 41:50.216
-How perfect was that, huh?
-Can it.

41:50.382 --> 41:53.719
-We’re so screwed.
-I’m on my last nerve as it is,

41:53.928 --> 41:56.597
so lose the stupid grin
or I’m gonna jump across this desk.

41:56.847 --> 41:58.807
-All right, guys. Come on.
-(JOHN CONTINUES LAUGHING)

42:00.476 --> 42:02.811
-Maybe I should take off, then.
-Good idea.

42:03.729 --> 42:05.189
-You got the fives?
-Yeah.

42:05.814 --> 42:08.108
You hurry up and get your ass
into happy hour.

42:08.526 --> 42:10.027
Read my mind. (CLEARS THROAT)

42:10.819 --> 42:12.530
Hey, first-day beer celebration on me.

42:13.197 --> 42:15.282
-I’m fine. thanks, though.
-JOHN: All right.

42:22.998 --> 42:26.252
-What are we gonna do, Andy?
-(SIGHS) Nothing.

42:27.044 --> 42:28.629
I ain’t changing a damn thing.
